{
  "texts": [
    "M. Goldblum et al. [49] shed light on the dataset processing vulnerabilities in ML model development.Various dataset exploits and their countermeasures are reviewed in [49] to analyze the security issues in the training and processing datasets.",
    "Many training-only attacks, such as bi-level optimization, label flipping, and feature collision attacks, are highlighted, specifically on deep neural networks (DNN).",
    "Similarly, some backdoor attacks are also studied.",
    "This research paper highlights the need to mitigate dataset poisoning, which is critical and complex.On the other hand, M. Regaki and S. Garcia [50] shed light on adversarial privacy attacks that pose another critical threat to machine learning.",
    "They studied literature from the past 7 years, with forty papers explaining the severity of privacy attacks in adversarial machine learning and their countermeasures."
  ]
}